AD_FIELD.NAME: Type
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A distinct item characteristic used for processes and sometimes grouped within a category.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Type indicates the type of validation that will occur. This can be SQL, Java Script or Java Language.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Datasource
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The datasource
AD_FIELD.HELP: The datasource provides data from the database or from in-memory data.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Client
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Client for this installation.
AD_FIELD.HELP: A Client is a company or a legal entity. You cannot share data between Clients.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Organization
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: Organizational entity within client
AD_FIELD.HELP: An organization is a unit of your client or legal entity - examples are store, department. You can share data between organizations.

AD_FIELD.NAME: HQL
AD_FIELD.HELP: A query HQL code.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Active
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: A flag indicating whether this record is available for use or de-activated.
AD_FIELD.HELP: There are two methods of making records unavailable in the system: One is to delete the record, the other is to de-activate the record. A de-activated record is not available for selection, but available for reporting. There are two reasons for de-activating and not deleting records: (1) The system requires the record for auditing purposes. (2) The record is referenced by other records. E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are existing invoices for it. By de-activating the Business Partner you prevent it from being used in future transactions.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Summarize Type
AD_FIELD.HELP: Select the desired summarize option in case the column is numeric and it is desired to have the sum, average,..

AD_FIELD.NAME: Width
AD_FIELD.HELP: Width of the column in percentage. If the sum of the widths is higher than 100 the grid will adapt the values. For example, 3 columns with 100 width will take 33% of the grid width each.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Reference
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The data type of this field.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Reference indicates the type of reference field

AD_FIELD.NAME: Reference Search Key
AD_FIELD.DESCRIPTION: The exact reference specification for a list or a table.
AD_FIELD.HELP: The Reference Value indicates where the reference values are stored. It must be specified if the data type is Table or List.

AD_FIELD.NAME: Include In
AD_FIELD.HELP: Sets the visibility of the column: - Widget view, column is shown on all cases. - Maximized view, column is shown only in maximized view and included in the exported file. - Exported file, column is only included in the exported file.

AD_FIELD.HELP: Flag to set that the field of the grid will have a link

AD_FIELD.NAME: Can be filtered
AD_FIELD.HELP:
This flag sets whether it is possible to filter the grid by this column or not on maximized view. To be able to filter it is also needed to set on the HQL Code where clause the display expression between @ symbols that will be replaced on execution by the filter clause in case it is being filtered or "1=1" when it is not.
For example: having the following HQL "select product.name as prodcutName from product". To be able to filter by product name it is needed to include a "where @productName@" in the where clause: "select product.name as prodcutName from product where @productName@"

AD_FIELD.NAME: Where Clause Left Part
AD_FIELD.HELP: Left part of the where clause needed to filter by a value of this column on the maximized view.
